# Final UI Polish & Bug Fixes Walkthrough

This document outlines the final polishing steps and critical bug fixes implemented for the portfolio builder application. 

## Final UI Testing & Polish
- Used an automated browser agent to fully test the UI form from end-to-end, injecting Maximum Data (multiple projects, deep arrays, very long text strings) to verify stability.
- The UI handles large amounts of data beautifully without breaking layout bounds.
- Noted a few UX improvements that could be iterated on (like dynamic navbar logos and form auto-scrolling).

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- A user can register, log in, create a portfolio using all dynamic arrays (Languages, Features, Tags, Responsibilities), and save successfully.

## 1. Dynamic Form Arrays
Replaced all comma/pipe-delimited string textareas with robust **Angular FormArrays**. 
- Users can now click `+ Add Item` to dynamically add specific inputs for Features, Technologies, Responsibilities, and Languages.
- Each item has its own dedicated input element and a remove button, significantly improving the UX.
- The [portfolio-form.ts](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/features/dashboard/components/portfolio-form/portfolio-form.ts) backend mapping logic was completely rewritten to submit structured arrays to the NestJS API cleanly.

## 2. Tagline Input Integration
Added a dedicated `Tagline` field inside the Personal Info step. 
- The Hero component was updated to prioritize this new Tagline field over the default job title fallback, giving users absolute control over their primary headline.

## 3. Custom CSS Scrollbars
Implemented custom webkit scrollbar styling globally in [styles.scss](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/styles.scss) using the `.scrollbar-custom` class. 
- Overflowing grids, textareas, and containers now feature a sleek, thin scrollbar with a custom track and a hoverable teal thumb that matches the global application theme.

## 4. Conditional UI Rendering
Fixed issues where static descriptive text or empty social links (like GitHub/LinkedIn buttons) would awkwardly appear even if the user provided no data for them.
- Deployed `@if` blocks across [hero.html](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/features/hero/hero.html) and [projects.html](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/features/projects/projects.html).
- Implemented intelligent protocol checking (`.startsWith('http')`) to ensure user-provided links don't break routing by appending `https://` universally if omitted.

## 5. Authentication Persistence Fix
Resolved a critical issue where hard-refreshing the dashboard logged the user out visually, despite their `HttpOnly` token remaining valid.
- **Backend**: Added a secure `GET /api/auth/me` endpoint in NestJS that decodes the HttpOnly JWT using the existing AuthGuard.
- **Frontend**: Created a [checkAuth()](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/services/auth.service.ts#46-57) method in the [AuthService](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/services/auth.service.ts#11-58) that pings this new endpoint and hydrates the `currentUser` signal.
- **Bootstrapping**: Leveraged Angular's `APP_INITIALIZER` token in [app.config.ts](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/app.config.ts). The Angular application now explicitly pauses its initial routing sequence until [checkAuth()](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/services/auth.service.ts#46-57) completes. This guarantees the AuthGuard has the correct session state before validating dashboard access!

## 6. UI Rendering Gap Fixes

We identified through our UI testing that several fields collected by the form and schema were missing from the public templates. We fixed these rendering bugs to maintain UI/Data parity:
- **Location**: Added conditional rendering to the [Hero](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/features/hero/hero.ts#5-56) section to display the user's location with an elegant pin icon beneath their job title.
- **Phone Number**: Updated the [Footer](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/core/layout/footer/footer.ts#7-17) contact section to include a properly formatted `tel:` link when a phone number is provided.
- **Education Description**: Updated the [Education](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-api/src/modules/portfolio/entities/education.entity.ts#10-36) timeline card to beautifully format and display the description field underneath the degree classification.

