## 7. Expanding Form Inputs for Database Schema Accuracy

While reviewing the TypeORM models for the portfolio architecture, we discovered several advanced fields (e.g. `Experience.projects`, `Experience.recognition`) were present in the backend but unreachable because they had no corresponding inputs in the Angular Form Builder. We added these nested `FormArray` and `FormGroup` elements into the Builder workflow:

```html
<!-- Added logic to handle parsing deeply nested arrays like Project Points -->
<div formArrayName="projects" class="space-y-4">
  @for (epCtrl of $any(expCtrl.get('projects')).controls; track epCtrl; let epIdx = $index) {
     <!-- Project Name, Tech Stack, and Bullet Points Array injected -->
  }
</div>
```

Testing verified that creating a Job with an embedded "Notable Project" and "Recognition" accurately compiled these fields into JSON, saved them to the PostgreSQL database, and dynamically rendered them onto the beautiful portfolio format.

- **Conditional Project Features**: If a user creates a project but leaves the "Key Features" list empty, the entire "Key Features" heading and its container are automatically hidden from the UI to prevent empty space in the project card.
- **Project Images**: Added a thumbnail image URL input for individual projects. If a thumbnail is supplied, the Tailwind CSS `object-cover` styling was corrected to ensure the image seamlessly stretches *edge-to-edge* across the project card padding, fixing a noticeable UI misalignment gap.

![Experience Section rendering DB DB-nested arrays](C:\Users\Rajnish\.gemini\antigravity\brain\19afe22d-2157-474f-89aa-6c86c50b8f4c\experience_advanced_v2_1772437095426.png)

## 8. Portfolio Privacy Toggles

During testing, we discovered the "Publicly Accessible" toggle inside the UI settings was passing boolean data to the database but was ignored by the backend data-fetching architecture. 

**Backend Fix:** 
- Updated [portfolio.service.ts](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/services/portfolio.service.ts) to block queries finding a portfolio by slug if `isPublic` is false *unless* the user requesting it is the owner.
- Created a custom NestJS [OptionalAuthGuard](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-api/src/common/guards/optional-auth.guard.ts#9-30) that non-intrusively parses `HttpOnly` JWTs if they exist in the browser request headers to identify portfolio owners without forcing a rigid `/login` redirect on anonymous visitors.

**Frontend Fix:**
- Adjusted the [HomeComponent](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/features/home/home.ts#16-64) (the main Public Portfolio viewer page) to catch HTTP 401 (Unauthorized) and 404 (Not Found) errors returned by the guarded API. Visually hanging screens are prevented by immediately redirecting the lost user back to the builder marketing homepage.
- Updated [portfolio.service.ts](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/services/portfolio.service.ts) to include `{ withCredentials: true }` on the `GET /portfolio/:slug` HTTP request. This securely attaches the owner's `HttpOnly` JWT cookie so the backend can verify their identity and allow them to preview their own private portfolios.

## 9. Routing UX Refinements

Based on manual testing, three critical UX routing flows were resolved:
- **Root URL Dead End**: Previously, visiting the bare root URL (`/`) would trap the user on an infinite "Loading Portfolio" screen because the router attempted to load a non-existent default slug. The root route was updated to permanently redirect to `/dashboard`. If the user has no active session, the Angular [authGuard](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/core/guards/auth.guard.ts#6-17) seamlessly escorts them back to `/login`.
- **Missing Sidebar User Data**: When a user logged in, their email wouldn't show up in the dashboard sidebar until they refreshed the page. This occurred because the backend `/login` endpoint wasn't returning the user object in its JSON response. We updated the NestJS [AuthController](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-api/src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts#11-59) to return the [id](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-api/src/shared/services/jwt.service.ts#18-21) and `email` immediately upon authenticating, hydrating the frontend signals instantly.
- **Login Route Protection**: Logged-in users who manually navigated back to `/login` or `/register` were presented with the authentication forms again. We implemented a [guestGuard](file:///e:/PROJECT/portfolio/portfolio-app/src/app/core/guards/guest.guard.ts#5-16) in the Angular Router that checks the active session and automatically bounces authenticated users safely back to their `/dashboard`.

The application is now highly resilient, feature-complete, and offers a premium user experience!
